laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated, fluid-filled, measuring 1 cm at the tip with mild surrounding fat stranding and an appendicolith at the appendiceal base. There is moderate colonic fecal load. No focal lesions or intrahepatic biliary duct dilatation in the liver. The kidneys show symmetric nephrograms with no lesions. No enlarged mesenteric or retroperitoneal lymph nodes.
